<div id="life">
<h2>Life</h2>

<img src="mother_teresa.jpg">
<p> Mother Teresa was a Roman Catholic nun who devoted her life to serving the poor and destitute, primarily in Calcutta, India.</p>
</div>

<div id="works">
<h2>Works</h2>
<p><b>Missionaries of Charity</b> - She founded this congregation to care for "the poorest of the poor" and those whom nobody else would look after.</p>
<p><b>Humanitarian Aid</b> - She established numerous clinics, orphanages, and hospices for people with leprosy, tuberculosis, and HIV/AIDS.</p>
<p><b>Global Advocacy</b> - She worked tirelessly to promote peace and human rights, receiving the Nobel Peace Prize in 1979 for her humanitarian efforts.</p>
</div>

<div id="legacy">
<h2>Legacy</h2>
<p>Mother Teresa's legacy is defined by her unconditional compassion and selflessness, inspiring millions to help those in need. She was canonized as a saint in 2016.</p>
